<param name="problem_name">_u4_m3_inlinetutor3</param>
</flash>-->
                </example>
                <p> </p>
            </body>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Comment</title>
            <body>
                <p>Notice that there are two types of problems we may want to solve: those like
                        <em>(a)</em>,
                    <em>(d)</em><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101122T095208-0500" content=","?>
                    and
                    <em>(e)</em><?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101122T095212-0500"?>,
                    in
                    which<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101122T095215-0500" content=" where"?>
                    a particular interval of values of a normal random variable is given, and we are
                    asked to find a probability, and those like <em>(b)</em>,
                    <em>(c)</em><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101122T095226-0500" content=","?>
                    and
                    <em>(f)</em><?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101122T095229-0500"?>,
                    in
                    which<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101122T095234-0500" content=" where"?>
                    a probability is given and we are asked to identify
                    wh<?oxy_insert_start author="mmyers" timestamp="20101122T095248-0500"?>at<?oxy_insert_end?><?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101122T095246-0500" content="ere"?>
                    the normal random variable's values would be.</p>
